cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper describes a robot-enabled image-based identification machine that uses computer vision to automate the process of invertebrate identification, biomass estimation, and sample sorting. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of state-of-the-art Resnet-50 and InceptionV3 CNNs for the classification task, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a robot to automate the process of invertebrate identification and biomass estimation suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper mentions the generation of a comprehensive image database of terrestrial arthropod species, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
